    "body": "### Feature already in Vim?\n\nNo\n\n### Feature description\n\nThere are tones of plugins which use signcolumn. (like gitsigns, lsp-config, todo-comments, nvim-ufo and so on)\r\nBut currently, since the SignColumn is located on the left side of the Number Line, the only way to prevent each Sign from overlapping is to increase the width of the SignColumn.\r\n\r\nI found that there is one column to the right of the NumberLine, it would be nice to use this space as an additional SignColumn.\r\n\r\nThis would prevent the Signs getting farther from the NumberLine.\r\n\r\nExamples:\r\n<img width=\"538\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/60088301/194818746-97556be6-0abc-4cec-b604-961accc05ea5.png\">\r\nIntellij's fold signs right side of the number line\r\n\r\n\r\n![](https://code.visualstudio.com/assets/docs/editor/codebasics/folding.png)\r\nVSCode's fold signs",
    "closed_at": "2022-10-11T00:43:07Z",
